    "summary": "LucFosther Diop was born in 1980(Douala-Cameroon). He studied Fine Arts at the Yaounde 1 University, from where he graduated in 2003. Two Artist Residencies in Douala followed: October 2003 at ArtBakery and April-May-June 2007 at MTNC Foundation. In 2006 he was part of the project-travel EXITOUR where a group of artists traveled trough seven West African countries. The project ended with an intervention at the Dakar Biennale. He has been Resident Artist at the Rijksakademie van beeldende kunsten(2009-2010).\n\nSelection of exhibitions in Cameroon and abroad:\n-'Ok Video International Festival', National Gallery, Jakarta, 2007.\n-'World One Minute Video Exhibition', Today Art Museum, Beijing, 2008.\n-'Identity: An Imagined State', CCA, Lagos, 2009.\n- 'First FIAC', National Museum of Contemporary and Modern Art, Alger, 2009.\n- 'Ceci produit Cela',  Contemporary art Centre Doual'art, Douala, 2010.\n- 'Contemporary African video art', International Rotterdam Film Festival, Rotterdam, 2010.\n- '16th International Symposium on Electronic Art', Dortmund, Essen and Duisburg, 2010.\n-'OF AMSTERDAM PREMIERE', SMART Project Space and Mediamatic Foundation, Amsterdam, 2012. \n-'Art Practices and Social Imaginaries', 11 Havana Biennal, Havana, 2012.\n-'Face Contact--Beijing', Iberia Center for Contemporary  Art, Beijing, 2012.\n-'Sanaa ya Makaratasi - African Paper Art: Process, Substance and Environment', Nairobi National Museum, Nairobi, 2012.\n\nOne of his video ''Attitudes'' was recently shown at the exhibition: Face Contact. Portrait and Communication, PHotoEspa\u00f1a11-International Photography and Visual Arts Festival, Teatro Fern\u00e1n G\u00f3mez Centro, Madrid, curated by Gerardo Mosquera. And his first video ''Around and Around '' has been shown in the program ''Forms and topographies : African Cityscape in flux'' curated by Dominique Fontaine at the 2nd Thessaloniki Biennale of Contemporary Art in 2009. He lives and works between Douala and Rotterdam.",
